07/31/80  COBOL Restrictions

The following is a list of various limits and restrictions as well as useful
clarifications which apply to the Multics COBOL compiler.


  - The allocation required for all items declared in the DATA
    DIVISION must not exceed 262,143 words.
  - The maximum number of files which can be declared in a program
    is 256.
  - Nonnumeric literal are limited to a length of 256 characters.
  - The maximum number of arguments which can be passed to a called
    program is 127.
  - The maximum length of a source program line is 255 characters.
  - The maximum size of the source and object programs is limited
    to one segment (i.e. 262,143 words).


